net.coderazzi.filters.parser.generic
Class StringWildcardOperand

java.lang.Object
  net.coderazzi.filters.parser.generic.StringWildcardOperand
All Implemented Interfaces:
IRelationalOperand
public class StringWildcardOperand
extends Object
implements IRelationalOperand

Operand associated to expressions with wilcards.

It accepts two wildcard characters, used as widely known in filesystems:

  • *: zero or more characters.
  • ?: exactly one character.
For example: A?m*s will match: Armies, Almanacs, ...

The implementation handles at one equal and distinct operators, case sensitive or insensitive

Author:
Luis M Pena - lu@coderazzi.net

createOperator

public IOperator createOperator(Object right)
Description copied from interface: IRelationalOperand
Creates an operator by applying an object on an operand. For example, in 'a < 3', the operand is '<', and creates the operator '<3' when associated to the right object 3. Returns null if the right object is not valid.
